Sasalin spewed a jet of flame, the tall Slakian igniting a small patch of forest before circling overhead, watching for the right moment. Strangely, when he slowed down, the strange screeching behind him also stopped. Sasalin had forgotten there was a passenger on his back.
"Come on, Tenruk, you've transformed into a Slakian before!"
"Flying on your own is completely different from suddenly being dragged away by a huge pink dragon!"
"It's okay, Kayer?"
Kayer obviously disagreed with Nishi's words; he looked paler than usual, and his claws had deeply embedded into Sasalin's back, drawing blood from the Slakian, but Sasalin clearly didn't care. That said, Sasalin realized he had scared his new friend and found an empty spot to land.
"Sorry, sorry, I smelled something. I need to deal with it!"
"Do you have to drag us along too?" Tenruk climbed down from Sasalin's back and slid down Sasalin's tail to the ground, asking sharply. "We left Retvik behind! We abandoned that strong, aggressive brute! How is he going to find us?"
"He'll figure it out..." Nishi nodded in agreement. "Retvik is slow, but he's not stupid."
"Will Retvik know how to drive?"
Nishi blinked and turned to look at Tenruk. "Of course he knows how to drive."
"Have you ever seen Retvik drive a car? He doesn't have a truck like you, and I've never seen him drive a cute little car like Kayer's. He only started taking the bus to work because you always drove us to work. He only has a bicycle."
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Sasalin suddenly burst into laughter, but no one knew what he was laughing at. It took Sasalin a while before he calmed down.
"Sorry, sorry, I just imagined your big, armored friend riding a little bicycle designed for Temson children. That image is so ridiculous! I wish I had telepathy. That idea is so funny! I definitely need to remember it!"
Kayer also laughed because he could imagine what Sasalin was thinking. "Alright, alright. But what did you smell? Why did you fly so fast?"
Sasalin hummed and took off, disappearing quickly before returning and dropping a corpse in front of Nishi. It was an Orosarack, a very rare golden-white dragon-like creature. But its head was missing. "Another one dead. I heard their screams. Smelled their blood. I have to protect them, hunt down the killer. This is Isyni's will. Those creatures are nearby."
The powerful Slakian suddenly froze. Nishi and Kayer also froze, their attention drawn to a gap at the edge of the clearing. A huge, pitch-black thing was staring at them, hissing. The creature suddenly spread its two pairs of massive wings and charged forward, directly at Sasalin, entirely unbothered by the three small beings blocking its path to Sasalin. Kayer and Tenruk barely managed to get out of the way, but Nishi found herself being thrown to the ground, almost onto Sasalin's back.
Sasalin grabbed Nishi, using his long and nimble tail to throw her onto his back, then took to the air. The black winged creature quickly gave chase.
Kayer muttered, drawing his rifle from behind and opening his bag to take out a bullet belt. He fastened the bullet belt across his chest for easy access, but quickly realized that Nishi, Sasalin, and the monster were no longer in sight.
"Hey, Tenruk, can you transform into a flying animal?" Kayer asked.
"You want to chase after them?"
"Nonsense."
"But... one of them is a giant monster!"
"So what? This rifle in my hand is powerful, and I can shoot anytime. I just need to see it, and I can bring it down."
Tenruk hesitated for a moment, then stepped back to give himself some space. With a low, slightly painful groan, Tenruk's body stretched out, his fur turning into scales, his arms transforming into wings. He soon became a regular light blue Slakian, but his eyes remained red.
"Get on."
Tenruk now looked like a fairly ordinary Slakian, with neatly arranged scales growing on his back and a pair of sharp spines, making it easier for Kayer to hold on. It took Tenruk a long time to take off, but once airborne, he quickly adjusted his direction and struggled to catch up.
However, Tenruk and Kayer soon realized they were not facing only one opponent. A second dark monster surged up from beneath them, and Tenruk barely dodged the impact.
"I guess this is the other terrifying big monster that Ranelux was worried about?" Kayer frowned, trying to shoot at the second monster but missing, quickly reloading his weapon.
Tenruk didn't respond; he was busy flying toward Nishi and Sasalin, despite the other monster chasing them. Kayer awkwardly turned around to face the monster. Kayer thought this was good news because it made it easier to aim and shoot. Two bullets pierced the monster's upper wing, and it roared in pain before disappearing into the forest. Kayer wasn't sure if it was still following them, but he felt certain it couldn't keep up anymore.
Up ahead, Sasalin was wildly writhing his body, spewing flames at the black monster, while Nishi desperately clung to Sasalin to avoid falling. Although this monster was certainly injured, it seemed enraged and unwilling to retreat, and the fireballs didn't seem to have caused much damage. After stabilizing himself, Sasalin allowed Nishi to take the opportunity to draw her weapon, a shotgun she trusted. Of course, the shotgun couldn't take down a monster like this, but the scattered bullets would at least scare off this black beast, right?
